      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be under version control with documented regression test suite covering turbulence and species transport modules.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used under a validated configuration management plan. Regression tests covering the k-omega SST turbulence model and scalar hemolysis transport were executed and passed. SQA level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification must be demonstrated for the primary flow solver and hemolysis scalar transport equation using manufactured solutions or benchmark problems.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests were completed for the Navier-Stokes solver (second-order confirmed) but the hemolysis power-law scalar transport term was only verified against a single published benchmark without systematic grid refinement. Achieved level 2 falls short of the required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for hemolysis index QoI across at least three systematically refined meshes at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (5 M, 12 M, 28 M cells) were used; GCI values for the hemolysis index ranged from 4.2% to 7.8% across the five operating points. Discretization error is within the accepted tolerance band. Level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be documented with uncertainty and replicated in the CFD model within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles from PIV are applied at the CFD inlet; however, fluid temperature was held constant at 22°C in experiments versus 37°C in the clinical COU. Viscosity correction was applied analytically but not experimentally validated. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., validation metric V, MAPE) must be reported for hemolysis index and velocity field QoIs with uncertainty intervals.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field comparisons show mean absolute error of 8.3% against PIV. Hemolysis index predictions are within 22% of bench measurements, which exceeds the 15% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoIs (hemolysis index, velocity magnitude) must be directly linked to the clinical decision QoI (patient hemolysis risk) through a documented traceability matrix.",
      "rationale": "A traceability matrix maps the modified index of hemolysis (MIH) measured in bench tests to the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used in the clinical threshold. The linkage is documented in the validation plan. Level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must span the full operating envelope of the COU (flow rates 3–7 L/min, speeds 2400–3600 RPM) with documented interpolation or extrapolation justification.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments cover 3 of 5 target operating points. The two highest-speed conditions (3400 and 3600 RPM) were not experimentally tested due to facility limitations. Extrapolation to those points is unvalidated. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residuals below 1e-5 for all equations; round-off error must be assessed via double-precision confirmation.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; scalar transport residuals reached 1e-5. Double-precision arithmetic confirmed. Solver error contribution to hemolysis index uncertainty is less than 0.5%. Level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented review process must confirm that model setup (boundary conditions, material properties, solver settings) was independently checked by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was reviewed by the lead analyst only; no independent second-analyst check was performed for the hemolysis scalar transport settings. This represents a use-error risk at MRL 3. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The choice of turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model must be justified by sensitivity analysis and comparison to higher-fidelity or alternative model forms.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST was selected based on prior literature for rotating machinery. A comparison to k-epsilon realizable was performed at one operating point only, showing 12% difference in hemolysis index. No LES comparison was performed. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in key model inputs (blood viscosity, hemolysis model constants C and alpha) must be quantified and propagated via Monte Carlo or equivalent method.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across 1000 samples varying viscosity (±5%), hemolysis constant C (±15%), and exponent alpha (±10%). 95th-percentile hemolysis index bounds are reported for all operating points. Level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Biological variability in blood analog fluid properties must be characterized across at least three independent sample lots; pump-to-pump geometric variability must be assessed.",
      "rationale": "A single lot of porcine blood analog was used for all bench hemolysis tests. Pump-to-pump geometric variability was not assessed; only one physical pump unit was tested. Sample representativeness is limited. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrate that the input parameter space of the validation experiment (geometry, fluid properties, operating conditions) is equivalent or conservatively bounding relative to the clinical COU input space.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that this factor does not apply to the current COU because the validation experiment uses the identical FDA generic pump geometry and nominally equivalent boundary conditions as the clinical model, making a formal equivalency demonstration unnecessary. Consequently no structured assessment was performed and no requiredLevel or achievedLevel was assigned. This judgment was not encoded as factorStatus 'not-applicable' in the package — the factor remains 'not-assessed' — leaving an unresolved epistemic gap at Model Risk Level 3."
    }
