    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the twelve assessed factors, taken together, provide sufficient evidence to support the hemolysis prediction claim under MRL 3. The Equivalency of input parameters factor was judged by the team to be inapplicable given the shared pump geometry between validation and clinical COU; accordingly no gap was recorded in the decision rationale. The package is submitted as Accepted. Note: the not-assessed status of the Equivalency factor — rather than the formally correct not-applicable encoding — constitutes an unresolved epistemic gap that was not considered in this decision.",
